  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>GE mainstream wall oven — mass-market base tier</h2>
    <p>Mainstream GE sits at the base mass-market tier of GE Appliances' four-tier wall oven hierarchy — below Profile (feature-focused premium), Café (style-first premium), and Monogram (ultra-luxury). Mainstream GE positions at $800-1.8k new-purchase price with standard bake + broil + convection capability, basic self-clean cycle, and practical control platform without smart-feature integration. This is the most common GE wall oven tier in LA's broad renovation market — the default spec for rental properties, starter homes, value-conscious kitchen updates, and installations where the wall oven isn't a differentiator.</p>
    <p>Haier Group has owned GE Appliances since 2016. Louisville Kentucky distribution supports mainstream GE service reliably including parts for older 10-15 year units. Common mainstream GE parts 2-4 day lead; specialty or pre-2010 components 5-7 days.</p>
  </div></section>

